article.headline: Deveny scores 16 of her 23 points in second half
article.linkText: Deveny's big second half rallies No. 20 Boston College
article.story:
BOSTON (AP) -- Jessalyn Deveny scored 16 of her team-high 23
points in the second half as Boston College (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today; No. 22 Associated Press) battled back
from an 11-point deficit to beat Temple 69-62 Saturday.

	   Deveny and Amber Jacobs combined on 6-for-6 shooting from the
foul line to secure the victory in the final minute.

	   Khadija Bowens' layup 57 seconds into the second half gave the
Owls (4-2) their biggest lead of the game at 33-22.

	   A 13-2 run by Boston College (4-1), behind seven points by Becky
Gottstein, tied the game 35-35 at 4:47.

	   The teams played through four more ties over the next few
minutes, before Boston College pulled away to a 61-54 lead with
2:33 to play on two free throws by Jacobs.

	   Christena Hamilton's 3-pointer brought Temple to 63-62
with 1:08 to play before the Eagles pulled away for good.

	   Candice Dupree led Temple with 23 points, on 10-for-15 shooting.
